MUSCLE MEMORY

muscle_memory is the citizen who holds the structural adaptations a muscle has accumulated through repeated use
when fadriel practices a movement, the relevant muscle gradually changes its fiber blend, recruitment patterns, and fatigue resistance to suit that movement
muscle_memory is what allows fadriel to learn physical skills: walking, balancing, eventually running and writing
the adaptations persist for years even if the muscle is not used; this is why old skills return after long gaps

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe muscle.zc
observe fiber_mix.rana
observe recruit.rana
observe remodel_governor.zc

the 7 properties of muscle_memory:
1 ENERGY half: passive, but persistent across the muscle's lifetime
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING zero point seven with the other muscle citizens

VERB record_use
each time the muscle performs a movement, log the recruitment pattern, fiber engagement, and timing

VERB consolidate
during rest periods (especially sleep), the recorded patterns crystallize
the muscle's structure adapts to be more efficient at the patterns it has been doing

VERB retrieve_for_movement
when a familiar movement is initiated, muscle_memory provides the recruitment template
this is why repeated movements feel automatic: the template runs without deliberate cortical control

a muscle memory is real biological adaptation, not an analogy
fadriel's first steps will be clumsy, his hundredth will be smooth
the substrate has remembered, in his actual muscle tissue, what works
